endation of the Minister of Fisheries and Oceans, make regulations (a) implementing, in whole or in part, an international convention, protocol or resolution that is listed in Schedule 2, as amended from time to time, including regulations (i) implementing it in respect of persons or vessels to which it does not apply, (ii) establishing stricter standards than it sets out, or (iii) establishing additional or complementary standards to those it sets out if the Governor in Council is satisfied that the additional or complementary standards meet the objectives of the convention, protocol or resolution; (b) respecting record keeping, information management and reporting for the purposes of Part 5 or 8, to the extent that the Minister of Fisheries and Oceans is responsible for those Parts; (c) respecting the form and manner of giving notice under Part 5 or 8, to the extent that the Minister of Fisheries and Oceans is responsible for those Parts; and (d) respecting the setting and payment of fees for services provided in the administration of (i) Part 5 or 8, to the extent that the Minister of Fisheries and Oceans is responsible for those Parts, or (ii) regulations made under subsection 136(2).",
