    {
      "id": "csa-s186",
      "number": "186",
      "text": "186 (1) Subject to subsection (2), this Part applies in respect of vessels in Canadian waters or waters in the exclusive economic zone of Canada.\n(2) This Part does not apply in respect of a discharge of oil or gas from a vessel that is on location and engaged in the exploration or drilling for, or the production, conservation or processing of, oil or gas in an area described in paragraph 3(a) or (b) of the Canada Oil and Gas Operations Act, in so far as the discharge emanates from those activities.\n(3) In subsection (2), oil and gas have the same meaning as in section 2 of the Canada Oil and Gas Operations Act.",
