    {
      "id": "csa-s237",
      "number": "237",
      "text": "237 Every rule and principle of the common law that renders any circumstance a justification or an excuse in relation to a charge for an offence under a relevant provision applies in respect of a violation to the extent that it is not inconsistent with this Act.",
