      "text": "268 (1) Subject to subsection (2), all fines imposed under this Act must, despite any other Act, be paid to the Receiver General and deposited to the credit of the Consolidated Revenue Fund.\n(2) A court, justice of the peace or provincial court judge who imposes a fine under this Act may direct that the whole or a portion of it may (a) be applied in compensating a person for any wrong or damage that may have been caused by the act or default in respect of which the fine was imposed; (b) be applied in or toward payment of the expenses of the proceedings; or (c) be paid to the provincial, municipal or local authority bearing in whole or in part the expense of prosecuting the contravention of this Act in respect of which the fine was imposed.",
